        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To provide PDF-specific utilities for page counting and page-to-image conversion, enabling the Dedoc pipeline to extract visual representations of PDF pages. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  PDF page count retrieval, PDF page image rendering. \par \b Input\/ \:  File path to PDF document, page index. \par \b Output\/ \:  Page count (int), page image (PIL.Image). \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(8): pypdf, pdf2image] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>get_pdf_page_count returns None (not raises) on unreadable PDFs.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>get_page_image returns None if no images rendered for the given page. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why use pypdf instead of PyPDF2? A: pypdf is the actively maintained successor with better error handling. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added SEMANTIC TEMPLATE markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>FUNC 7[PDF page count] =&gt; get_pdf_page_count FUNC 8[PDF page to PIL image] =&gt; get_page_image \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[get_pdf_page_count]: Reader → AssessDocumentLength → Page count reported</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>[get_page_image]: StructureExtractor → ExtractVisualFeatures → Page image rendered </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
